{"cursor":"1553","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Open peer commentary' consists of eliciting (and publishing) non-anonymous\ncommentary on a peer-reviewed \"target article\" from a dozen or more specialists\nacross disciplines, co-published with the author's response. It was first\nimplemented by the anthropologist Sol Tax, who founded the journal\nCurrent Anthropology, published by University of Chicago Press in 1959. The\njournal Behavioral and Brain Sciences, published by Cambridge University Press,\nwas founded by Stevan Harnad in 1978 and modeled on Current\nAnthropology's open peer commentary feature. New Scientist, 20 March 1980,\n[http://books.google.com/books?id=_qVe8jMDAB4C&pg=PA945 p. 945] Psycoloquy\nwas founded in 1990 on the basis of the same feature, but this time\nimplemented online.\n","linknr":104,"url":"Open_Peer_Commentary","recorded":1375088672,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Open_peer_commentary&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Open_peer_commentary&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Open_peer_commentary","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Open_Peer_Commentary&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Sol_Tax","#cite_note-1","/wiki/Current_Anthropology","/wiki/University_of_Chicago_Press",